[medium] src/composables/useAiDiagnostics.ts:102 (concurrency/races)
loadMoreRuns has no in-flight guard and the view disables the Load More button only with runsLoading, which tracks the initial refresh request rather than the separate runsPageRequest. A double-click or repeated activation before the first page resolves can send multiple requests with the same nextCursor and append the same page more than once, corrupting the loaded run list.
Suggested fix: Expose the page request isLoading state from useDataApi, return it from useAiDiagnostics as paginationLoading, guard loadMoreRuns when paginationLoading is true, and disable the Load More button with runsLoading || paginationLoading.
Guidance: In src/composables/useAiDiagnostics.ts, expose and use the pagination request loading state. Change the runsPageRequest useDataApi destructuring to include isLoading, for example const { execute: runsPageRequest, isLoading: paginationLoading } = useDataApi<AiDiagnosticsRun[]>(...). At the start of loadMoreRuns, return early when !nextCursor.value or paginationLoading.value is true, before clearing paginationError. Add paginationLoading to the returned object. In src/views/admin/AiDiagnosticsView.vue, destructure paginationLoading from useAiDiagnostics(), and update the Load More SecondaryButton disabled binding from :disabled="runsLoading" to :disabled="runsLoading || paginationLoading". Do not use runsLoading for pagination in the composable, and do not dedupe appended rows after the fact; prevent duplicate same-cursor requests before they start.

